<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Built-in compactor repair pencils through year 12-15. Free-standing leans replace at year 8+.</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Trash compactors are a niche residential appliance — most LA homes we service have either a built-in under-counter unit (KitchenAid Architect, Whirlpool Gold, GE Profile) integrated into kitchen millwork, or a free-standing model in a utility room or pantry. The repair-vs-replace math differs significantly between the two.</p>
      <p>Built-in units at year 8-12 with a single-component failure (ram motor, drive gear, switch) usually pencil as repair because replacement requires removing the existing unit, modifying cabinetry to fit a new compactor (sizes vary by model), and reinstalling — total cost usually exceeds the repair. Free-standing units at year 8+ with a major repair like ram motor ($380-$540) on a $400-$700 retail unit usually lean replace.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block">
      <div class="tip-label">&#128126; Charcoal filter is 3-6 month maintenance, not a repair</div>
      <p>Most "smell" complaints we get on trash compactors trace to overdue charcoal filter replacement. Filter is a $40-$80 part the operator can replace; many LA households haven't replaced theirs in 2+ years. We replace it on every service visit when overdue.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
